Wani masanin ilimi ya gano cewa a jami'a mafi girma a duniya, mutane ba su san ainihin yadda za su kula da kansu ba.
Charles Chesler, farfesa a fannin maganin bacci a Harvard Medical School kuma kwararre a asibitin Brigham da Women's Hospital, ya tsara wani tsari, wanda ake ganin shine na farko a Amurka.
Ya fara wannan darasin ne bayan ya yi jawabi game da tasirin rashin barci a kan ilimi.
A ƙarshen makarantar, wata yarinya ta zo wurina kuma ta ce, "Me ya sa aka gaya mini wannan lokacin da nake shekara ta ƙarshe?"
Ta ce ba wanda ya taɓa gaya mata muhimmancin barci, abin mamaki, in ji ta ga jaridar The Telegraph.
Wannan karatun, wanda aka gabatar a karon farko a wannan shekarar, ya bayyana wa ɗalibai yadda samun isasshen barci yake da muhimmanci ga ɗalibai da 'yan wasa don inganta ayyukansu da kuma lafiyarsu.
Paul Brierera, farfesa a fannin ilimin halayyar dan adam a Harvard Medical School kuma darektan zartarwa na jami'ar kiwon lafiya, ya ce jami'ar ta yanke shawarar fara karatun ne bayan an gano cewa dalibai sun kasance masu fama da matsalar rashin bacci a cikin mako guda.
Wannan darasi na awa ɗaya yana ɗauke da jerin maƙasudai masu ma'amala.
A wani sashe akwai hotunan ɗakin kwana inda ɗalibai ke shan kofi, da labule, masu koyarwa, da littattafai da ke magana game da tasirin maganin kafeyin da haske da kuma yadda rashin barci ke shafar aikin 'yan wasa da kuma mahimmancin daidaita lokacin bacci.
