HIV/AIDS: Sabbin cututtuka sun karu da kashi 14 cikin 100 a China
Kasar Sin ta bayyana cewa yawan mutanen da ke dauke da cutar HIV da AIDS ya karu da kashi 14 cikin dari.
Jami'an kiwon lafiya sun ce mutane sama da 8,20,000 ne ke fama da cutar a kasar.
A cikin kwata na biyu na 2018 kadai, an samu sabbin mutane kusan 40,000.
Yawancin sabbin mutane da suka kamu da cutar sun kamu da cutar ta hanyar jima'i, wanda ke nuna canjin da aka samu a baya.
A al'adance, cutar HIV tana yaduwa cikin sauri a wasu yankunan kasar Sin ta hanyar bayar da jini mai cutarwa.
Amma, jami'an lafiya na kasar Sin sun ce, wannan hanyar ta kawo raguwar yawan masu dauke da cutar HIV zuwa kusan babu.
Duk da haka, a kowace shekara, adadin mutanen da ke fama da cutar HIV da AIDS a ƙasar Sin ya ƙaru da mutane 100,000.
Yaduwar cutar HIV ta hanyar jima'i babbar matsala ce a cikin al'ummar LGBT na kasar Sin.
A kasar Sin, an hana luwadi aikata laifi tun shekara ta 1997, amma nuna bambanci ga mutanen LGBT ya karu a ko'ina.
Binciken ya nuna cewa kimanin kashi 70-90 cikin dari na maza da ke yin jima'i da maza a kasar suna auren mata saboda dabi'un kasar da suka saba da al'ada.
Rashin kariya a cikin irin wannan dangantaka shine dalilin da ya sa yawancin cututtuka ke faruwa.
Tun daga 2003, gwamnatin kasar Sin ta yi alkawarin samar da maganin HIV ga kowa a duniya a matsayin wani bangare na kokarin magance matsalar.
